# Wireframe Specification

## Required Wireframe Screens

The following wireframes illustrate the main features of the Smart Campus Event Hub. Each screen represents a key part of the user journey and supports the project's MVP requirements. All wireframes should be exported as PNG files.

| Wireframe File | Purpose | Minimum Elements to Show | Related Requirements |
|---|---|---|---|
| /wireframes/homepage.png | Entry point of the system | Project title, welcome message, navigation bar, search bar, featured/upcoming events, main action buttons | FR-01, FR-03 |
| /wireframes/event-list.png | Display all campus events | Event cards or list, category, date, organizer, search box, filter options, event status | FR-01, FR-03, FR-10 |
| /wireframes/event-details.png | Display complete event information | Event title, description, date, time, location, organizer, registration button, event status | FR-04, FR-05 |
| /wireframes/event-registration.png | Student event registration | Registration form, student information fields, submit button, confirmation/error message | FR-05 |
| /wireframes/calendar-view.png | Display events in calendar format | Calendar, highlighted event dates, monthly navigation, selected event details | FR-08 |
| /wireframes/admin-dashboard.png | Event management for organizers | Dashboard summary, total events, participant list, create/edit/delete event buttons, publish event option | FR-02, FR-09, FR-10 |

## Wireframe Quality Rules

- Use a consistent layout, navigation bar, and design across all screens.
- Include realistic sample event information instead of empty placeholders.
- Ensure every wireframe represents a meaningful system function.
- Clearly show the user flow from browsing events to event registration.
- Every screen should support one or more functional requirements (FRs) defined in the project documentation.
- Wireframes may be created using Figma, Canva, PowerPoint, HTML/CSS, or another suitable design tool.
- Export every completed wireframe as a PNG image.
